00:29:30,835 --> 00:29:33,827
Nothing. It's nothing.

344
00:29:34,239 --> 00:29:36,036
It can't be nothing.

345
00:29:38,376 --> 00:29:39,866
Just jitters.

346
00:29:41,980 --> 00:29:45,313
Lila, are you sure
you want to go through with this?

347
00:29:55,293 --> 00:29:58,228
So Carl announces, quite proudly

348
00:29:58,696 --> 00:30:02,359
that when he grows up,
he's not going to marry Mum after all.

349
00:30:03,401 --> 00:30:06,268
He's going to marry Jean Harlow.

350
00:30:08,373 --> 00:30:13,572
Well, he's done a lot better
than Jean Harlow, in my humble opinion.

351
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:16,207
Welcome to the family, Lila.

352
00:30:16,281 --> 00:30:17,714
Thank you.

353
00:30:17,949 --> 00:30:20,782
I hope you know
what you're getting yourself into.

354
00:30:21,186 --> 00:30:22,813
Hear, hear, hear.

355
00:30:26,624 --> 00:30:28,751
Well, I am the very proud father of...

356
00:30:28,827 --> 00:30:31,591
Hey, Sis! Hey, Sis!
You know what you've got, Sis?

357
00:30:33,565 --> 00:30:37,001
You have got a talent for love.

358
00:30:39,470 --> 00:30:41,529
You're like a love genius.

359
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:47,177
And there's too many statues of generals
and politicians,

360
00:30:47,245 --> 00:30:50,214
and there's not enough statues
of someone like you.

361
00:30:50,281 --> 00:30:51,680
You know.

362
00:30:56,421 --> 00:31:02,257
But in this world, in this world
there's so much of what looks like love,

363
00:31:03,361 --> 00:31:07,627
and sounds like love, and it calls itself love

364
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:10,857
but it isn't.

365
00:31:13,972 --> 00:31:18,602
It's just people saying and doing

366
00:31:18,676 --> 00:31:22,772
what they think
that they ought to say and do.

367
00:31:27,452 --> 00:31:28,851
And you...

368
00:31:41,199 --> 00:31:42,826
You're the greatest.

369
00:31:45,136 --> 00:31:46,626
You're the greatest.

370
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:54,005
So here's to love.

371
00:31:55,179 --> 00:31:56,942
And here's to you.

372
00:32:07,325 --> 00:32:09,122
Buddy, how about we put you to bed?

373
00:32:09,193 --> 00:32:10,387
Party's not over is it?

374
00:32:10,461 --> 00:32:11,928
Come on, son.

375
00:32:11,996 --> 00:32:13,930
We were just gonna go
for a little walk, weren't we?

376
00:32:13,998 --> 00:32:15,488
Buddy and me.

377
00:32:15,566 --> 00:32:18,831
A walk would be just exhilarating
right about now.

378
00:32:26,411 --> 00:32:27,935
Excuse me, sir.

379
00:32:29,914 --> 00:32:32,815
...Lila listens to reason.
We've got to talk her out of it.

380
00:32:32,884 --> 00:32:35,079
I guess we would be the ones.

381
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:37,922
Ann, come here.

382
00:32:38,056 --> 00:32:39,148
Oh!

383
00:32:39,223 --> 00:32:41,919
Buddy, Buddy. How about sitting down?

384
00:32:42,126 --> 00:32:44,526
Yeah. Maybe that's a good idea.

385
00:32:45,830 --> 00:32:47,320
No, no, no.

386
00:32:51,936 --> 00:32:53,460
Hey, beauties.

387
00:32:57,942 --> 00:32:59,239
Buddy.

388
00:33:02,380 --> 00:33:06,146
Why do I feel like he's been this way
since he was about 10?

389
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:09,481
He didn't actually start drinking
until he was 12.

390
00:33:13,758 --> 00:33:16,022
He's a total disaster, really.

391
00:33:18,696 --> 00:33:20,857
And yet, I seem to love him.

392
00:33:21,866 --> 00:33:23,697
Yeah, I love him, too.

393
00:33:37,949 --> 00:33:40,383
Okay, he's all tucked in.

394
00:33:42,086 --> 00:33:45,180
You've been doing this a long time,
haven't you?

395
00:33:46,124 --> 00:33:48,888
Before he settled down he showed me
the star he picked out for you.

396
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,291
Oh, that.

397
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:54,093
It's a nice little star.

398
00:33:54,165 --> 00:33:57,896
It is. It's very nice.
It's one of the Seven Sisters.

399
00:33:59,637 --> 00:34:02,606
See? There she is, right there.

400
00:34:05,009 --> 00:34:06,636
This isn't too personal, is it?

401
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:08,474
No. No, not really.

402
00:34:09,881 --> 00:34:11,781
I met Buddy in college,

403
00:34:11,849 --> 00:34:14,977
and within three weeks
he'd picked me out a star,

404
00:34:15,286 --> 00:34:20,883
he'd declared my flower to be the peony,
my bird to be the swift,

405
00:34:20,958 --> 00:34:25,657
my tree to be the sycamore,
the list goes on.

406
00:34:26,664 --> 00:34:28,222
He was in love with you.

407
00:34:28,299 --> 00:34:32,702
No. No, he was
my best friend's little brother.

408
00:34:34,338 --> 00:34:37,000
But as we would walk around campus
and he'd go on

409
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:40,602
about how the swift was my bird,
the onyx was my stone,

410
00:34:42,146 --> 00:34:47,140
I finally asked him why he kept doing that
and do you know what he said?

411
00:34:49,454 --> 00:34:52,389
He said he did it
so that I would remember him

412
00:34:52,457 --> 00:34:57,520
whenever I saw peonies and swifts
and sycamores and all that.

413
00:34:59,964 --> 00:35:03,866
As if he just thought
he would disappear one day.

414
00:35:06,070 --> 00:35:07,594
Isn't that sad?

415
00:35:13,144 --> 00:35:15,578
See that star over there?

416
00:35:16,614 --> 00:35:17,945
Where?

417
00:35:18,015 --> 00:35:19,744
The medium-sized,

418
00:35:20,451 --> 00:35:23,477
right there, the one near Orion.

419
00:35:26,958 --> 00:35:28,050
Yes.

420
00:35:30,061 --> 00:35:31,153
Hey.

421
00:35:34,065 --> 00:35:35,623
That's our star.

422
00:35:36,234 --> 00:35:40,295
It's the one we were looking at
when you were a beautiful young girl

423
00:35:40,371 --> 00:35:44,273
kissed by some strange older guy
